Hi,

In file SimplePositionProvider.java when methods "locationManager.requestLocationUpdates()" and "locationManager.removeUpdates()" are called at runtime is thrown and exception that says:

"Call requires permission which may be rejected by user".

There is a fix for this problem ( replace methods "startUpdates()" and "stopUpdates()" with:

``` java
    public void startUpdates() {
        if(locationManager != null) {
            if (checkSelfPermission(context, Manifest.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION) == PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED
                    || checkSelfPermission(context, Manifest.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION) == PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED) {
                locationManager.requestLocationUpdates(type, period, 0, this);
            }
        }
    }
```

``` java
    public void stopUpdates() {
        if(locationManager != null) {
            if (checkSelfPermission(context, Manifest.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION) == PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED
                    || checkSelfPermission(context, Manifest.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION) == PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED) {

                locationManager.removeUpdates(this);
            }
        }
    }
```

